The article discusses President Obama's plan to create a better bargain for the middle class by ensuring that every American who is willing to work has the opportunity for a good job that pays good wages. The plan includes simplifying the tax code for businesses, eliminating loopholes that encourage companies to ship jobs overseas, and establishing a top tax rate of 28%. The President also proposes using one-time revenues raised from the transition to a new business tax system to invest in infrastructure, create manufacturing hubs, and train workers for future jobs. The article also mentions additional executive actions and efforts to spur job growth, such as attracting foreign investment and supporting the long-term unemployed. The President also calls for increasing the minimum wage, supporting U.S. exports, strengthening manufacturing communities, and increasing investments in clean energy research.